snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Brad. I have watched some of your videos and think they are great. You give really good advice! So my question for you:
'How can you grow your hair faster?'

Just a disclaimer though. I am not asking for myself. My hair is stupidly healthy and grows stupidly fast. And I am very happy about that, but my little sister is not as fortunate. Her hair has always been quite dry, prone to split ends and prone to breaking, and will easily grease. If that wasn't enough, her hair grows very slowly. Her former days as a dancer, where hair spray, all kinds of hair irons and brushing the hair the opposite way to obtain a bigger hairstyle, and the like, was the norm didn't really help either. She has tried coconut oil and olive oil and honey treatments and anything that might help (with proper research beforehand of course, since she doesn't want to make it worse).
With all these treatments her hair has softened and is less dry than before she started these treatments, but it's far for perfect... Her biggest problem is the slow hair growth.
Have you got any good advice?
